snippet.textDisplay: The beauty of most Coke studio performances is breathtaking in how they show the best fusion of East and West in melody and rhythm. Just see how the stringed instruments especially the violins provide transitions to the main voice here and then, toward the end, support the very brief but precious part of the back-up singers. Beyond the beautiful singing by Sajjad Ali, those musical segments are all so enchanting in themselves that I become transported to a dreamland. Of course, the baansuri, the guitar and the percussion instruments only contribute more to the magic.

snippet.textDisplay: We often use gold as a metaphor for the smoothness and glow of a voice.Well I want to ask: Is there gold above 24 carats in purity? Such may not exist in real life, but Sajjad Ali's voice is that gold in my fantasy. When I heard him sing Baghon Mein Pade Jhoole, I believed he had matched if not exceeded the beauty of Ghulam Ali's rendition. I still do.
